dplyr

Published

February 26, 2024

dplyr is a grammar of data manipulation, providing a consistent set of verbs that help you solve the most common data manipulation challenges.

setup

library(dplyr)
library(medicaldata)

data

  • Streptomycin for Tuberculosis Dataset
strep_tb
  • COVID-19 Testing Dataset
covid_testing
  • Theophylline Pharmacokinetics Dataset
theoph

filter

strep_tb |> 
  filter(arm == "Control")
strep_tb |> 
  filter(arm == "Control", gender == "M")
strep_tb |> 
  filter(arm == "Control" & gender == "M")

pull

strep_tb |> 
  pull(patient_id)
